DOC.brief_summary: This study will evaluate the safety and efficacy of two different types of botulinum toxin type A for the treatment of glabellar frown lines.
DOC.brief_title: Safety and Efficacy of Two Types of Botulinum Toxin Type A For the Treatment of Glabellar Lines
DOC.criteria: Moderate to severe glabellar frown lines Diagnosis of myasthenia gravis or Eaton Lambert syndrome Aesthetic treatment with botulinum toxin within 6 months or planned treatment with botulinum toxin for any reason during the study Prior filler treatments, surgeries, insertion procedures in/to the glabellar region Facial cosmetic procedures in the glabellar area within 6 months Bleeding disorders or use of anticoagulants within 10 days History of facial nerve palsy
